Jeanette Chabalala, News24Bloemfontein &ndash; Free State police are investigating a case of murder after a man was stabbed and shot dead during a house robbery in Thubelisha in Thabong, police said on Tuesday. &nbsp;Solomon Matabela Jorose, 29, was at home with his wife on Friday night when they heard noises outside their house, Sergeant Mamello Mokhuoane said. &nbsp; When he went outside to check, four men grabbed, stabbed and shot him, said Mokhuoane. He was declared dead on scene. &nbsp;The four suspects later ransacked the man&rsquo;s house and demanded money from the wife. They took five cellphones and R1 000. &nbsp;&nbsp;No arrest had yet been made. &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.